        overview1: "Travel bans (mana' al-safar) are one of the most powerful enforcement tools available to creditors in Saudi Arabia — court orders that prohibit a debtor from leaving the Kingdom until a debt or judgment is satisfied. Saudi enforcement courts have broad authority to impose travel bans on individual judgment debtors and on the directors, officers, and authorised signatories of corporate debtors — making flight from the Kingdom effectively impossible and creating enormous pressure on debtors to settle. Travel bans can be applied for as part of enforcement proceedings once a judgment has been obtained, or in some circumstances as a precautionary measure during proceedings. Qanoni applies for travel bans urgently as part of a comprehensive enforcement strategy — maximizing pressure on debtors and accelerating recovery.",
