        seoTitle: "Mediation & ADR Lawyer in Saudi Arabia | Online Dispute Resolution Consultation | Qanoni",
        subtitle: "Expert guidance in commercial mediation and alternative dispute resolution — achieving efficient, confidential settlements before costly arbitration or litigation.",
        overview1: "Mediation and alternative dispute resolution (ADR) offer parties the opportunity to resolve commercial disputes faster, at lower cost, and with greater flexibility than arbitration or court litigation — while preserving commercial relationships and maintaining complete confidentiality. Saudi Arabia's Legal Proceedings Before Sharia Courts Law and the Saudi Centre for Commercial Arbitration (SCCA) Mediation Rules provide a recognised framework for commercial mediation in the Kingdom. Qanoni advises and represents clients in commercial mediation and ADR processes — from pre-dispute contract negotiation clauses through structured mediation proceedings — with a focus on achieving cost-effective, commercially sensible resolutions.",
        overview2: "Mediation is increasingly included in commercial contracts in Saudi Arabia — both as a standalone dispute resolution mechanism and as a required step before arbitration or litigation. Where mediation is contractually required, failing to attempt it in good faith can prejudice your legal position. Where mediation is optional, a well-prepared mediation strategy can achieve a settlement that preserves value on both sides. Qanoni advises on when to pursue mediation, how to prepare effectively, and how to achieve the best possible outcome.",
        experienceNote: "Qanoni's ADR practice spans commercial contract disputes, construction disagreements, joint venture conflicts, and employment disputes — with extensive experience in preparing clients for and representing them in mediation proceedings, and in drafting dispute resolution clauses that protect client interests across the full spectrum of outcome scenarios.",
