        overview1: "International commercial arbitration has become the standard dispute resolution mechanism for cross-border commercial transactions involving Saudi parties — whether under ICC, LCIA, UNCITRAL, SCCA, or other institutional rules. Saudi businesses, government entities, and foreign investors with Saudi interests regularly find themselves as parties to international arbitration proceedings — seated in Paris, London, Geneva, Dubai, Riyadh, or other arbitration centres. Qanoni provides expert representation in international commercial arbitration proceedings involving Saudi law, Saudi parties, or Saudi-related contracts — combining deep knowledge of Saudi substantive law with procedural experience in the major international arbitration institutions.",
