        overview1: "Investment arbitration — the resolution of disputes between foreign investors and host states under bilateral investment treaties (BITs), multilateral investment treaties, or investment contracts — represents the most specialised and high-stakes area of international dispute resolution. Saudi Arabia is party to a network of bilateral investment treaties providing foreign investors with substantive legal protections including fair and equitable treatment, protection from unlawful expropriation, and access to international arbitration — typically before ICSID (the International Centre for Settlement of Investment Disputes) or under UNCITRAL rules. Qanoni advises and represents foreign investors and Saudi-connected parties in investment arbitration proceedings — combining deep Saudi law expertise with international investment law experience.",
        overview2: "Investment arbitration claims often arise from government actions that adversely affect foreign investments — including regulatory changes, licence revocations, contract terminations, expropriation of assets, or discriminatory treatment by Saudi authorities. Identifying whether these actions breach applicable investment treaty protections requires specialist analysis of the relevant BIT, the nature of the government conduct, and the investment arbitration case law. Qanoni advises immediately on receipt of any adverse government action against a foreign investment — assessing whether treaty protections apply and what remedies are available.",
